text: Pinagong is a dense bread roll from the Philippines made with all-purpose flour, milk, and salt. It is a variant of pan de monja (monáy) distinguished primarily by its shape and the more complex pattern of scoring on top. The name means "made into a turtle", from Tagalog pagong ("turtle"). ==See also== *Putok *Pandesal * List of bread rolls == References == Category:Philippine breads Category:Yeast breads
